19:10.867 --> 19:15.514
My wife and I, we've been married now.

19:15.834 --> 19:19.299
We're about to complete our 22nd year of marriage.

19:19.319 --> 19:20.100
Wow, I feel old.

19:21.221 --> 19:24.786
Yeah, please clap for that and send gifts.

19:27.970 --> 19:30.373
And we have three daughters.

19:31.154 --> 19:33.377
Now, I mentioned one of them who's a senior in high school.

19:33.397 --> 19:36.901
We also have an eighth grader and we have a fourth grade.

19:36.941 --> 19:38.063
Okay, fourth grade.

19:38.183 --> 19:38.684
Yeah, I got you.

19:38.804 --> 19:39.465
I got you.

19:39.485 --> 19:39.965
She's right here.

19:40.426 --> 19:41.247
She's gonna keep me to it.

19:42.108 --> 19:44.251
Now, listen, there's a lot of teenagers in my life.

19:44.992 --> 19:49.337
In our student ministry, there's upwards of 600 kids over there on a Wednesday night.

19:49.618 --> 19:50.759
I got all these college students.

19:50.839 --> 19:51.540
I love you guys.

19:51.560 --> 19:54.304
Good to see you all there with me on Tuesday nights.

19:54.324 --> 19:54.844
And they're great.

19:54.985 --> 19:56.146
I love the teenagers.

19:56.450 --> 19:58.773
They'll call to this, excited to be with them.

19:59.955 --> 20:01.557
I'll even invite them over to my house.

20:01.837 --> 20:04.841
You guys can come hang out, but you're leaving at nine.

20:06.604 --> 20:08.426
Get out of my house, right?

20:09.167 --> 20:13.333
I mean, it's fine, you can come over, you can eat some food, don't eat that food, that's mine.

20:15.896 --> 20:26.290
I'll hang out with you, but there are only three people in this world that are my kids, and it's different.

20:28.450 --> 20:31.915
My daughters always have a seat at my dinner table.

20:31.935 --> 20:32.275
Always.

20:34.078 --> 20:36.481
Ellie, when you graduate, you just come back every weekend.

20:36.561 --> 20:37.022
It'll be great.

20:37.722 --> 20:38.083
Always.

20:40.206 --> 20:42.289
My daughters all have their own bedroom.

20:43.751 --> 20:44.732
They live with us.

20:45.653 --> 20:48.617
They have their own space in my home.

20:49.538 --> 20:50.640
My daughters know me.

20:50.700 --> 20:52.823
Man, they seen me in a robe and slippers this morning.

20:53.984 --> 20:55.186
They know me different.

20:55.266 --> 20:56.267
than these teenagers.

20:56.627 --> 20:58.489
They've seen my ups, they've seen my downs.

20:58.789 --> 20:59.790
They know me.

21:01.132 --> 21:02.473
They have access to me.

21:03.674 --> 21:05.295
They could come to me at any moment.

21:05.336 --> 21:10.520
Now, when they were little, they like to interrupt bathroom time and I'd be like, this is daddy time, you know, like, go away.

21:12.342 --> 21:14.784
But they know they can come to me at any moment.

21:15.385 --> 21:16.526
This is the gift.

21:17.747 --> 21:20.250
The gift is not my stuff, although it is.

21:20.330 --> 21:22.392
Everything I have is theirs, believe me.

21:23.333 --> 21:24.914
They will take it all, right?

21:26.434 --> 21:27.115
It's all theirs.

21:29.638 --> 21:32.101
But the gift is so much more valuable.

21:32.141 --> 21:33.202
The gift is us.

21:34.764 --> 21:36.626
The gift is our relationship.

21:37.407 --> 21:38.368
The gift is love.

21:38.529 --> 21:41.672
It's all about the relationship.

21:43.174 --> 21:44.155
And you know this too.

21:44.236 --> 21:46.538
That we can pursue success.

21:46.819 --> 21:49.322
We can pursue all these other things in life.

21:49.342 --> 21:52.405
But at the end of the day, it's all about the relationship.

21:52.626 --> 21:56.210
This is what the prodigal son's story was that Jesus told quickly.

21:57.730 --> 22:06.321
We think that the prodigal son's story is about two sons, the younger son who didn't want anything to do with his dad, so he sold the inheritance.

22:06.562 --> 22:09.365
He wanted to go live out from under his dad's rules and his roof.

22:09.606 --> 22:21.842
He wanted to be on his own, do his own thing until he quickly came to his senses, as it says, ran out of money, was broke, destitute, and realized I had it so much better in the presence of my father.

22:23.714 --> 22:26.217
So he comes home right, he'll even be a slave.

22:26.257 --> 22:31.664
He just wants to be with his dad, even if it's as a slave and his dad robs him and throws him the party.

22:31.684 --> 22:32.385
You remember this.

22:32.965 --> 22:38.052
And then the older brothers like, wait a second, he did all that and you're accepting him back into this family.

22:38.312 --> 22:41.276
And you remember the fathers like pleading with him, come to the party.

22:41.496 --> 22:45.741
Let's celebrate your brother and he wouldn't go.

22:46.402 --> 22:50.427
You see the prodigal son's story is not about the boys.

22:51.608 --> 22:52.850
It's about a father.

22:53.058 --> 22:54.800
who just wanted to be with his kids.

22:56.943 --> 23:09.480
The gift that you have and I have this Christmas season is a God who invites you in the relationship with him, not religion, not check the box, do your divo on a Monday morning so that we're cool.

23:10.241 --> 23:10.902
Don't you see?

23:10.962 --> 23:20.114
The gift is just to be with him, let him speak into your life, let him lead you, let him encourage you, walk with him, know him.

23:21.314 --> 23:22.956
This is the gift he invites us into.

23:23.156 --> 23:27.740
Advent is a season that calls us first and foremost to just receive his presence.

23:28.041 --> 23:31.804
The word became flesh and dwelt with us.

23:35.188 --> 23:41.534
The gift is him, but let me say this.

23:41.574 --> 23:49.522
It's also the gift of others because a family is not just you and the parent.

23:49.698 --> 23:51.722
or as a parent, it's not just you and your kid.

23:52.043 --> 23:59.298
For many of you that just experienced Thanksgiving again, you recognize it wasn't just a house with me and my parent or me and the kids.

23:59.478 --> 24:07.314
There are aunts, uncles, cousins, in-laws, grandchildren, children, all of them are the family and don't miss this.

24:07.586 --> 24:17.541
Because not only is this Advent season about receiving the gift of with, it's a call for us as the family of God adopted into this to be with one another.

24:17.962 --> 24:28.278
You have been called to give the gift of with, to enter in and engage with the people around you and kind of speak to the men for just a minute.

24:30.461 --> 24:36.210
Sunday mornings, first Baptist is not just a building and a church, it's a family.

24:36.482 --> 24:38.124
It's actually an eternal family.

24:39.005 --> 24:45.813
And no matter what our situations are in life, this family says that whatever you're going through, you don't go through alone.

24:46.073 --> 24:53.182
And it's a call for us to be engaged, to enter in, to be a part of this and not just a spectator.

24:54.423 --> 24:58.388
So many men, I'm gonna tell you, I'm not here to disciple your kid as the student pastor.

25:00.751 --> 25:03.314
I'm here to partner with you, but I only get an hour within.

25:05.314 --> 25:07.537
Some of our kids don't have fathers.

25:08.098 --> 25:09.099
Would you disciple them?

25:09.279 --> 25:12.483
Would you pour into these kids coming up in our church?

25:12.503 --> 25:13.925
Because they're part of our family.

25:14.225 --> 25:20.734
The call is for us all in whatever capacity we can to give the gift of with as well, to engage.

25:23.637 --> 25:28.564
When Ellie was two years old, we would go on donut dates.

25:28.584 --> 25:29.525
We started this thing.

25:31.307 --> 25:32.549
I was like, man, I'm gonna be a good dad.

25:32.569 --> 25:33.650
I'm gonna be in her life.

25:34.082 --> 25:37.808
worked all week, but on Fridays, I'm taking off, we're going to get donuts.

25:37.828 --> 25:39.591
And we'd get donuts, and then we'd go to the park.

25:40.212 --> 25:41.274
We'd go play at the park, right?

25:42.416 --> 25:43.057
It was our thing.

25:43.217 --> 25:46.242
And as I had more kids, we kept this tradition alive.

25:46.382 --> 25:47.985
Every Friday, it was a donut day with Dad.

25:48.345 --> 25:53.233
I have all these photos, in my Google photos, of them growing through the years at a shipless donut.

25:53.293 --> 25:53.874
It was awesome.

25:54.916 --> 25:58.522
But there would be times where we couldn't go to the park because it was raining.

25:59.503 --> 26:01.106
And so I had to make something up.

26:01.474 --> 26:03.216
play hide and go seek or do some of that.

26:03.556 --> 26:04.637
And I'll never forget this.

26:04.818 --> 26:06.339
Ellie was seven years old.

26:07.861 --> 26:10.264
And one day we go get donuts and it's raining.

26:11.505 --> 26:12.646
And so we have to come to the house.

26:12.766 --> 26:14.408
And I'm like, okay, well, we can't go to the park.

26:14.468 --> 26:18.292
What if we drew photos or a picture of us going to the park?

26:19.033 --> 26:19.674
That would be fun.

26:20.395 --> 26:21.296
And so I was like, great.

26:21.356 --> 26:22.297
Yeah, I'll do that.

26:22.317 --> 26:22.917
I like to draw.

26:23.438 --> 26:25.480
And so we're both drawing our photos, y'all.

26:26.922 --> 26:29.365
And then I see her finished photo.

26:30.145 --> 26:30.706
Let me show you.

26:31.394 --> 26:43.168
I don't know if you can make this out, but my seven-year-old draws a photo of her going down a slide, having the time of her life going, Wee, this is awesome!

26:44.109 --> 26:48.694
And then she draws me at the bottom of the slide, catching her involved, no.

26:49.515 --> 26:55.442
Y'all, that's a photo of me on a park bench looking at my phone.

27:00.898 --> 27:02.500
Hashtag dad fail.

27:03.662 --> 27:05.925
Man, that one hurt, y'all.

27:06.325 --> 27:09.029
I'm like, yeah, dad has to answer a few texts.

27:09.109 --> 27:12.173
Maybe it's answered an email while we're on our daddy daughter date.

27:12.414 --> 27:18.842
But man, I was like present for 3.3 hours and 50 minutes of the four hour time, right?

27:18.922 --> 27:20.444
You just saw me in my phone.

27:20.865 --> 27:21.566
It doesn't matter.

27:23.148 --> 27:24.410
That was her picture.

27:26.352 --> 27:30.578
There is a difference church family with being around

27:32.450 --> 27:33.251
and being with.

27:36.534 --> 27:47.406
There is a difference between having proximity to people around you and engaging and being loving and sharing and being involved.

27:47.426 --> 27:51.231
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

27:51.251 --> 28:00.261
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

28:00.281 --> 28:01.522
We'll see you next week.

